      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/protocol/coders/ProtocolCoderToolset.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 327,
      "message": "I'm unsure about this one.  I could imagine that we end up having to deal with xml instead of json for some API, but not sure.  I could also imagine that someone might want a gson coder that uses jackson behaviors, so at this point it kind of makes sense to me to keep this abstraction layer.",
